<br>
At best a Warrior tries to be clever about aggro, disciplines, deciding when to split tank, when to back off, etc. Yet Clerics shift from MT CH rotation, spot healing, saving a key raid member, etc. with a high level view of the fight that is sometimes astounding. Enchanters cooly slow, tash. charm, mezz adds, buff during battle, cover for each other, etc. despite the fact that they wear &quot;Kill Me&quot; signs on their backs for every mob to see.<br>
<br>
I don't mean to overlook Necros, Shamen, Druids, etc. I just want to keep this post a reasonable length. I've seen all of these classes have a huge impact on fights against named mobs - waaaaay beyond what I thought their capablities were. I know all high level players respect members of these classes. But, I seldom hear the praise they are due.<br>
<br>
Looking from their vantage point high above the clash of swords and screams of the dying, the support classes find a path to victory.<br>
<br>
